00034 // some common macros
00035 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00036 
00037 #define MSB(x)  (((x) >> 8) & 0xff)     // most signif. byte of 2-byte integer
00038 #define LSB(x)  ((x) & 0xff)            // least signif. byte of 2-byte integer
00039 #define MSW(x) (((x) >> 16) & 0xffff)  // most signif. word of 2-word integer
00040 #define LSW(x) ((x) & 0xffff)          // least signif. byte of 2-word integer
00041 
00042 
00043 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00044 // Macro for converting Phys.Addr (X.X.X) into EIBPA (=WORD) and
00045 //           converting Grp.Addr  (X/X/X) into EIBGA (=WORD)
00046 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00047 // PA :  z=zone  l=line  d=device
00048 // GA :  a=1st   b=2nd   c=3rd      (use 3-level Group addresses)
00049 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00050 
00051 #define PA(z,l,d)    (EIBPA) (((DWORD)(BYTE)(z & 0x0F)<<12)|((DWORD)(BYTE)(l & 0x0F)<<8)|(BYTE)(d & 0xFF))
00052 #define GA(a,b,c)    (EIBGA) (((DWORD)(BYTE)(a & 0x1F)<<11)|((DWORD)(BYTE)(b & 0x07)<<8)|(BYTE)(c & 0xFF))
00053 
00054 
00055 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00056 // Macro to Set Fields within the EIB Message Frame
00057 //-----------------------------------------------------------------
00058 
00059 //--- set physical address
00060 #define SetPA(msg,pa)   msg[4] = MSB(pa); msg[5] = LSB(pa)
00061 
00062 //--- set group address
00063 #define SetGA(msg,ga)   msg[4] = MSB(ga); msg[5] = LSB(ga)
00064 
00065 //--- set sequence count
00066 #define SetSC(msg,sc)   msg[7] = (msg[7] & 0xC3) | ((sc & 0x0F) << 2)
